properties.headline: Wind Chill Advisory issued January 24 at 7:37PM AKST until January 25 at 3:00PM AKST by NWS Fairbanks, AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Very cold wind chills to 45 expected. The cold wind
chills will cause frostbite in as little as 10 minutes to
exposed skin.

* WHERE...Over the Baldwin Peninsula including Kotzebue.

* WHEN...Now to 3 PM Saturday.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The strongest winds and coldest wind
chills are near Kotzebue. Winds are much lighter inland at
Selawik and Noorvik, and wind chills are less severe at those
locations.
properties.instruction:
A Wind Chill Advisory means that cold air and sustained wind
speeds of 15 mph or more will create low wind chills. Frost bite
and hypothermia can occur if precautions are not taken.

NWSheadline: WIND CHILL ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 PM AKST SATURDAY
